{{!
    @template filter_fastpix/player

    The player mount wrapper for a {fastpix:pb_<id>} embed. Mirrors
    mod_fastpix/player_wrapper attribute-for-attribute, MINUS every
    watch-tracking attribute and the completion UI — embeds are casual viewing,
    mod_fastpix owns completion (invariants 5 and 6). Specifically removed vs
    the activity wrapper: data-session-token, data-cm-id, data-activity-id,
    data-asset-id, data-no-skip-required, data-current-position, data-threshold,
    data-asset-duration, the completed-indicator block and the intro lede.

    The AMD module filter_fastpix/player_boot reads these data-* attributes and
    mounts the <fastpix-player> web component (it is NOT a literal element here,
    matching the activity's JS-mount pattern). data-drm-token is intentionally
    EMPTY at render: the DRM token is fetched client-side on first play
    (invariant 8), so it never lands in cacheable page HTML.

    Player attribute names are pinned to the @fastpix/fp-player public surface
    (CC9). Renaming without reading upstream docs is a CC9 violation — the
    player silently renders an inert black box if attrs drift.

    Context variables:
      * playbackid     string
      * playbacktoken  string  (manifest JWT; empty for public assets)
      * drmrequired    bool
      * accentcolor    string|null
      * expiresatts    int     (unix seconds)
      * videotitle     string  (asset title; CC9 metadata-video-title)

    Example context (json):
    {
        "playbackid": "abc123",
        "playbacktoken": "jwt",
        "drmrequired": false,
        "accentcolor": "#ec1e5b",
        "expiresatts": 0,
        "videotitle": "Welcome video"
    }
}}
<div class="filter_fastpix-player-wrapper"
     data-region="fastpix-player-wrapper"
     data-playback-id="{{playbackid}}"
     data-playback-token="{{playbacktoken}}"
     data-drm-token=""
     data-drm-required="{{#drmrequired}}1{{/drmrequired}}{{^drmrequired}}0{{/drmrequired}}"
     data-accent-color="{{accentcolor}}"
     data-video-title="{{videotitle}}"
     data-expires-at="{{expiresatts}}">
</div>
